<Link id="l02389" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2389"><Highlight kind="normal">&#125;</Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02390" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2390"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02391" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2391"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02392" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2392"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// guessLibraryShortName() is passed a name of a dynamic library and returns a</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02393" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2393"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// guess on what the short name is.  Then name is returned as a substring of the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02394" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2394"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// StringRef Name passed in.  The name of the dynamic library is recognized as</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02395" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2395"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// a framework if it has one of the two following forms:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02396" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2396"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      Foo.framework/Versions/A/Foo</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02397" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2397"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      Foo.framework/Foo</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02398" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2398"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Where A and Foo can be any string.  And may contain a trailing suffix</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02399" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2399"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// starting with an underbar.  If the Name is recognized as a framework then</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02400" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2400"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// isFramework is set to true else it is set to false.  If the Name has a</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02401" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2401"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// suffix then Suffix is set to the substring in Name that contains the suffix</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02402" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2402"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// else it is set to a NULL StringRef.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02403" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2403"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02404" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2404"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The Name of the dynamic library is recognized as a library name if it has</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02405" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2405"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// one of the two following forms:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02406" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2406"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      libFoo.A.dylib</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02407" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2407"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      libFoo.dylib</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02408" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2408"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02409" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2409"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The library may have a suffix trailing the name Foo of the form:</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02410" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2410"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      libFoo&#95;profile.A.dylib</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02411" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2411"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//      libFoo&#95;profile.dylib</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02412" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2412"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// These dyld image suffixes are separated from the short name by a &#39;&#95;&#39;</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02413" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2413"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// character. Because the &#39;&#95;&#39; character is commonly used to separate words in</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02414" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2414"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// filenames guessLibraryShortName() cannot reliably separate a dylib&#39;s short</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02415" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2415"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// name from an arbitrary image suffix; imagine if both the short name and the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02416" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2416"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// suffix contains an &#39;&#95;&#39; character! To better deal with this ambiguity,</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02417" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2417"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// guessLibraryShortName() will recognize only &quot;&#95;debug&quot; and &quot;&#95;profile&quot; as valid</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02418" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2418"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// Suffix values. Calling code needs to be tolerant of guessLibraryShortName()</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02419" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2419"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// guessing incorrectly.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02420" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2420"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l02421" /><CodeLine lineNumber="2421"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The Name of the dynamic library is also recognized as a library name if it</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>

<Link id="l03182" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3182"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// We have a trie data structure and need a way to walk it that is compatible</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03183" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3183"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// with the C++ iterator model. The solution is a non-recursive depth first</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03184" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3184"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// traversal where the iterator contains a stack of parent nodes along with a</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03185" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3185"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// string that is the accumulation of all edge strings along the parent chain</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03186" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3186"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// to this point.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03187" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3187"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03188" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3188"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// There is one &quot;export&quot; node for each exported symbol.  But because some</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03189" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3189"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// symbols may be a prefix of another symbol (e.g. &#95;dup and &#95;dup2), an export</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03190" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3190"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// node may have child nodes too.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03191" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3191"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">//</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03192" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3192"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// The algorithm for moveNext() is to keep moving down the leftmost unvisited</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03193" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3193"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// child until hitting a node with no children (which is an export node or</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03194" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3194"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// else the trie is malformed). On the way down, each node is pushed on the</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03195" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3195"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// stack ivar.  If there is no more ways down, it pops up one and tries to go</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
<Link id="l03196" /><CodeLine lineNumber="3196"><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight><Highlight kind="comment">// down a sibling path until a childless node is reached.</Highlight><Highlight kind="normal"></Highlight></CodeLine>
